author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Pushed to Gerrit as change 795 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/795). Extracted new pure leaf src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py (263 LOC, in [100,800]); det_floor.py 971 -> 746 LOC (<= 800 soft cap). Graduated det_floor off the module-size gate (removed from allowlist + ceilings; arch.md offenders row deleted). Widened the stale arch.md det_verify_lint.py seam to three islands (verify-lint + G5 decomposition-veto + task-DAG graph helpers) because the verify-lint cluster alone is sub-floor and left det_floor over cap. Validation: make lint clean; 140/140 named suites (test_module_size_contract, test_plan_review, test_g5_decomp_det, test_det_floor_operator_attested, test_det_invariants) pass; broader plan_review/pass1 sweep 376 passed. Awaiting Gerrit gates (LLM-Review + Verified); NOT submitting/closing per split playbook.","timestamp":1784398954785495001}],"created_at":1784397466611342001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py` is a grandfathered over-cap module (currently 971 LOC; soft cap 800). It carries a row in `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`, `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` (975), and a remedy row in docs/architecture.md. This story graduates it off the module-size gate by extracting a cohesive leaf of pure helpers.\n\n## What\n\nCreate a new pure leaf module `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py` (DetResult-free, re-only deterministic text/graph helpers), mirroring the existing sibling `det_operator_attested.py`. MOVE three cohesive islands out of det_floor:\n\n1. Verify-command lint (G-3a / WS4): `_VERIFY_*`, `_GREP_*`, `_SHELL_VAR_RE`, `_lint_verify_command`, `_verify_command_strings`.\n2. G5 decomposition-veto cluster: `decomposition_state_block`, `_G5_UNDECOMPOSED_RE`, `_is_undecomposed_claim`, `veto_undecomposed_g5`.\n3. Pure task-DAG graph helpers: `_find_cycle`, `_file_interference`.\n\nThe `DET_CHECKS` registry and all p1-p9 check functions STAY in det_floor. `p5_task_dag` real-imports `_find_cycle`/`_file_interference`; `p6_ac_quality` real-imports `_lint_verify_command`/`_verify_command_strings`; det_floor re-exports `decomposition_state_block`/`veto_undecomposed_g5` (# noqa: F401) for pass1.py + test_g5_decomp_det.py. The leaf references `PlanContext` only as a type annotation, imported under `if TYPE_CHECKING` with `from __future__ import annotations` first, so it is a true runtime leaf (no runtime import of det_floor).\n\n## DEVIATION from docs/architecture.md remedy row\n\nThe arch.md offenders row proposes extracting ONLY the verify-command-lint cluster into `det_verify_lint.py`. That row is superseded: the verify-lint cluster alone is SUB-FLOOR (<100 LOC) AND would leave det_floor still over the 800 cap. This ticket therefore WIDENS the seam — it moves the verify-lint island, the G5 decomposition-veto island, and the pure graph helpers (`_find_cycle`/`_file_interference`) into one `det_lint.py` leaf. The stale arch.md row is deleted by this ticket. This is a pure, mechanical refactor (no signature/logic change; symbols relocated + re-exported); E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing tests are the oracle.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] New leaf `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py` exists and is in [100, 800] LOC (verify: wc -l)\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py` is <= 800 LOC (verify: wc -l)\n- [ ] det_floor.py removed from .github/module-size-allowlist.txt AND .github/module-size-ceilings.txt; its docs/architecture.md offenders-table row deleted (verify: grep -c det_floor on all three)\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py passes (verify: python -m pytest that file -q)\n- [ ] Back-compat: det_floor still exposes decomposition_state_block and veto_undecomposed_g5 (re-exported); pass1.py and test_g5_decomp_det.py unchanged\n- [ ] Named suites green: python -m pytest tests/unit/test_plan_review.py tests/unit/test_g5_decomp_det.py tests/unit/test_det_floor_operator_attested.py tests/unit/test_det_invariants.py -q","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py","reason":"new pure leaf: verify-command lint + G5 decomposition-veto + task-DAG graph helpers moved here"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py","reason":"remove moved symbols; add re-import/re-export of moved helpers; graduates under 800 LOC"},{"path":".github/module-size-allowlist.txt","reason":"remove det_floor.py row (drops back under soft cap)"},{"path":".github/module-size-ceilings.txt","reason":"remove det_floor.py ceiling row"},{"path":"docs/architecture.md","reason":"delete det_floor.py offenders-table remedy row (stale/superseded seam)"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","716f-b917-9fc8-41f5"]],"parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_status_uuid":"51033fd3-f388-4c61-ab33-fe33260a9645","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["module-size"],"ticket_id":"e73b-71d5-e6d5-4d28","ticket_type":"story","title":"Split det_floor.py: extract pure text/graph helpers into det_lint.py leaf","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["85718173-2c1c-452f-869c-da9c8cb9b733","c5b82699-35a6-4098-acb8-68f32c07745b","6a90bc2a-0a4d-4ef2-bd97-e50c2e94cb06","51033fd3-f388-4c61-ab33-fe33260a9645","89a9c65f-3855-4402-94c7-6b3384d3e2b9","0802bd2e-2217-4eb2-8fea-0c8d4c47c857","205e1df7-fd5a-40ba-a0e1-76a8bc943bfe"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784399940953450058,"uuid":"f7b2690a-6b59-4f9f-9723-bee4b88a4d2b"}